      • validateReference

        public static boolean validateReference​(AbstractTableReference reference,
                                        boolean prompt)
        This method performs the model validation on an AbstractTableReference.
        Parameters:
        reference - the AbstractTableReference that is being validated.
        prompt - the flag that indicates whether messages should be added to the MessageWindow while performing the validation.
        Returns:
        TRUE if the table size matches the expected size, and all of the columns are mapped to valid table variable columns.

      • validateReference

        public static boolean validateReference​(AbstractTableReference reference,
                                        ColumnDescription[] columns,
                                        boolean prompt)
        This method performs the model validation on an AbstractTableReference.
        Parameters:
        reference - the AbstractTableReference that is being validated.
        columns - the ColumnDescription[] that contains the model table column data.
        prompt - the flag that indicates whether messages should be added to the MessageWindow while performing the validation.
        Returns:
        TRUE if the table size matches the expected size, and all of the columns are mapped to valid table variable columns.

      • validateReference

        public static boolean validateReference​(AbstractTableReference reference,
                                        SharedTable shared,
                                        ColumnDescription[] columns,
                                        boolean prompt)
        This method performs the model validation on an AbstractTableReference. This method requires a non-null shared table reference.
        Parameters:
        reference - the AbstractTableReference that is being validated.
        shared - the SharedTable that is referenced by the AbstractTableReference.
        columns - the ColumnDescription[] that contains the model table column data.
        prompt - the flag that indicates whether messages should be added to the MessageWindow while performing the validation.
        Returns:
        TRUE if the table size matches the expected size, and all of the columns are mapped to valid table variable columns.
